  "texts": [
    "Right: the corresponding sensitivity curve, i.e.",
    "area coverage vs. flux limit in the 0.6-2.3 keV band, for different galactic latitude intervals.",
    "systematic offset with the eRASS1 results may be related to e.g.",
    "uncertainties in the sensitivity calculations of the ROSAT sample, or the inclusion of more extended sources in RBS because of the larger ROSAT PSF.There is a significant excess for the source population at low Galactic latitude.",
